[{"Code":"en","Title":"Maya","Slug":"maya","ContentType":2,"Content":"<p data-block-id=\"4855e908-bced-4d3d-b759-6cb3ce5dd720\"><img data-block-id=\"affa9524-8d26-45f2-bc1c-65d32ce74489\" src=\"https://cdn.document360.io/217abc43-8677-41fb-a81d-fceeb1fa0358/Images/Documentation/autodesk-maya-logo-png-file.png\" class=\"adv-wysiwyg-img\" mediatype=\"img\" alt=\"\" width=\"217\" height=\"62\" dataalign=\"left\" datadisplay=\"flex\" data-type=\"media-content\" fixaspectratio=\"false\" autoaspectratio=\"true\" shadow=\"no\" border=\"no\" round=\"no\" link=\"\" newtab=\"\" style=\"width:217px;height:62px;\"></p><p data-block-id=\"f13b21d6-5f91-4b0a-bc30-c61d528f2b0e\">Maya (formerly known as PayMaya) is one of the most popular digital payment platforms in the Philippines, offering a comprehensive suite of financial services, including mobile wallet payments, virtual and physical cards, and banking features through Maya Bank. It is a highly trusted payment method for both online and offline transactions, with millions of active users across the country.</p><p data-block-id=\"783bc94d-6813-4218-866b-c0f67707bfb9\">Maya's versatility makes it a preferred choice among consumers and businesses. Customers can use Maya for a wide range of transactions, from online shopping and bill payments to money transfers and QR payments in physical stores. For businesses, integrating Maya as a payment option means access to a growing user base and the ability to offer a cashless, seamless payment experience.</p><hr class=\"hr-divider1\"><h2 data-block-id=\"6146dcc6-4245-4158-a034-de0971f8c50b\">Features</h2><div data-type=\"table-content\"><table width=\"926\" class=\"editor360-table\" borderstyle=\"solid\" style=\"max-width:926px;width:926px;\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:463px;\"><col style=\"width:463px;\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" colwidth=\"463\" style=\"overflow:hidden;padding:2px 3px 2px 3px;vertical-align:bottom;\"><p data-block-id=\"402452f7-7a96-45f3-